"title": "Job 1:1–5",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "18001001-18001005",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p><span data-bnType=\"resourceReference\" data-resourceId=\"108524\" data-resourceType=\"BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms\">Job</span> had everything that people in his time could hope for. He had a large family and many servants. He was a successful farmer of livestock. He was highly respected and had authority in the area where he lived.</p><p>He was also completely committed to <span data-bnType=\"resourceReference\" data-resourceId=\"108199\" data-resourceType=\"BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms\">God</span>. He did what God wanted done. He showed how much he respected God by making <span data-bnType=\"resourceReference\" data-resourceId=\"108256\" data-resourceType=\"BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms\">sacrifices</span>. He did this when his family <span data-bnType=\"resourceReference\" data-resourceId=\"108195\" data-resourceType=\"BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms\">sinned</span>. He even did it when he thought they might have sinned.</p><p>He wanted everyone in his family to live in ways that were considered <span data-bnType=\"resourceReference\" data-resourceId=\"108364\" data-resourceType=\"BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms\">pure</span> and <span data-bnType=\"resourceReference\" data-resourceId=\"108363\" data-resourceType=\"BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms\">clean</span>. This would allow them to worship God together.</p>",
